---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Containing X — Top Scoring X Words"
  description="Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words containing X. Free list of top X words with point values and strategy tips for placing X on premium squares."
  keywords="scrabble words containing x, x words scrabble, words with x, high scoring x words, scrabble x strategy, scrabble word list"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words Containing X — Top Highest-Scoring X Words",
    "description": "Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words containing X. Complete list with point values and premium square strategy.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-containing-x" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the highest-scoring Scrabble word containing X?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "MAXIMIZE scores 20 points without premium squares. Other high-scoring X words include EXACTLY (19 points), HEXAGON (18 points), and OXYGEN (17 points). X is worth 8 points, making it the third most valuable tile." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Where should you place X on the Scrabble board?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Always aim to place X on a double or triple letter square. X on DLS = 16 points from one tile; X on TLS = 24 points. Short X words like AX, OX, and EX are ideal for reaching these squares in tight positions." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What two-letter words contain X in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The valid two-letter X words are AX (9 points), EX (9 points), OX (9 points), and XI (9 points). All score 9 points — among the highest-scoring two-letter words. They're essential for parallel plays and tight board positions." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">More Letter Guides</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Containing X — Top Highest-Scoring X Words</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        X is worth 8 points and appears on only one tile in the bag, making it a premium draw every time. Unlike Q, X doesn't need a specific partner letter — it works in hundreds of positions across the board. From short tactical plays like AX and OX to longer scoring machines like OXYGEN and EXOTIC, X-containing words are the bread and butter of high-scoring Scrabble.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 30 Highest-Scoring Words Containing X</h2>
      <p>These are the most valuable words containing X, ranked by base point value. X's versatility means you'll find plays at every word length, from 2-letter hooks to 7+ letter bingos.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Length</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MAXIMIZE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">20</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXACTLY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">19</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HEXAGON</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXPIRY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXCLAIM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">OXYGEN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GALAXY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXOTIC</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXTOL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PIXEL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why X-Containing Words Matter in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>X is arguably the best tile in Scrabble relative to its difficulty. Worth 8 points (third-highest after Q and Z), X requires no specific companion letter and fits into an enormous range of words. Unlike Q, which needs U most of the time, X works naturally in positions throughout English — at the start (XENON), middle (EXOTIC, OXYGEN), and end (FOX, WAX) of words.</p>
      <p>The four two-letter X words — AX, EX, OX, XI — are particularly powerful. Each scores 9 points for just two letters, and they enable parallel plays that generate 20+ points from tight board positions. When you draw X, you should almost never exchange it. Between the two-letter plays for tight spots, medium words like EXOTIC (15 pts) and OXYGEN (17 pts) for open boards, and longer plays like MAXIMIZE (20 pts) and EXACTLY (19 pts) for bingo potential, X always has a home.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Always target premium squares:</strong> X on DLS = 16 points, X on TLS = 24 points from one tile. Short X words (AX, OX, EX) are ideal for reaching these squares in tight positions.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Learn all four 2-letter X words:</strong> AX, EX, OX, XI — memorise these for parallel plays. They turn any adjacent word into a multi-word scoring opportunity.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>X in the middle scores best:</strong> Words like EXOTIC, OXYGEN, and HEXAGON place X centrally where it can hit premium squares while the word extends in both directions.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Never exchange X:</strong> Unlike Q, X always has a valid play available. Even in the worst case, AX or OX scores 9 points. Hold X and look for premium square access.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>EX- prefix words are plentiful:</strong> EXOTIC, EXACTLY, EXCLAIM, EXPIRY, EXTOL — the EX- prefix gives you dozens of options from common rack letters.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-q/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing Q — Top Scoring Q Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-j/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing J — Top Scoring J Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending With X — Top Scoring X-Ending Words</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
